{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"37a25971-5d66-44ec-8b9b-014967f032e9","content":"Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** these packages:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Add** this property to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n   This enables `dotnet test` integration with MTP.\n\n4. **Enable the entry point** — add:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>true</GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n   Or, if you already have `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>`, write your own `Program.cs` entry point.\n\n5. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   # or directly:\n   dotnet run\n   ```\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n- MTP runs your test project as an executable, not via `vstest.console`.\n- CLI flags change: use `--filter` → `--treenode-filter`, `--logger` → `--report-*`, etc.\n- If you use `runsettings`, check compatibility — MTP supports a subset.\n\nWould you like help applying these changes to a specific `.csproj` file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"aae662ee-9ebf-4397-b7ca-1235e6faa948","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using `xunit.runner.visualstudio`) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":449},"id":"5645d953-231d-4ccf-a25f-e790bff749e2","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:54:19.889Z","parentId":"9f8e556a-f741-4795-9fb0-e7fe625ecd80"}
